shaped, down curved beak. Males usually have bigger beaks and more color compared to the females which have smaller beaks and a more dull color. More dull feathers and a bigger beaks distinguishes the Kaua'i 'amakihi from the other ʻamakihi species. Conservation The Kauaʻi ʻamakihi has been categorized as Endangered by the IUCN. As of 2023, this species has an estimated population of 2,200 – 4,400 mature individuals, which is decreasing. The Kauaʻi ʻamakihi is threatened by habitat loss, invasive species, and diseases such as avian pox and avian malaria. References External links Species factsheet - BirdLife International Videos, photos and sounds - Internet Bird Collectio", "shortSummary": "The Kauaʻi ʻamakihi (Chlorodrepanis stejnegeri) is a species of Hawaiian honeycreepers endemic to Kauaʻi in the family Fringillidae. The sp…", "habitats": ["峡谷峭壁", "开阔山地", "沼泽"], "threats": ["栖息地破坏"], "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/98/Kauai_%27amakihi.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-chlorodrepanis", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-chlorodrepanis-stejnegeri", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-chlorodrepanis", "species": "taxonomy-species-chlorodrepanis-stejnegeri"}, "expandable": true, "x": -556.71, "y": 822.9, "z": -664.0}, {"id": "taxonomy-species-chlorodrepanis-stejnegeri", "name": "Kauaʻi ʻamakihi", "latinName": "Chlorodrepanis stejnegeri", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "species", "summary": "Kauaʻi ʻamakihi（Chlorodrepanis stejnegeri）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联1种鸟类，如Kauaʻi ʻamakihi。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 1, "x": -556.71, "y": 822.9, "z": -652.61}], "links": [{"key": "bird-kaua-i-amakihi-2b553872__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-chlorodrepanis-stejnegeri", "source": "bird-kaua-i-amakihi-2b553872", "ta